dc:author: Herlihy, David
Klapisch-Zuber, Christiane
prov:wasDerivedFrom.dc:publisher: Presses de la Fondation Nationale des Sciences Politiques/École des Hautes Études en Sciences Sociales

dc:title.@value: Tuscans and their families: a study of the Florentine catasto of 1427

columns.name: NUMSER
columns.dc:description: Serial number describing geographic subdivision of Florentine territory

columns.name: NUMFAM
columns.dc:description: Household number within each territorial subdivision (NUMSER)

columns.name: QUART
columns.dc:description: Quarter, major subdivision of florentine contado,

columns.name: PIVIER
columns.dc:description: Pievere, further geographical subdivision within quarters. Within Florence, Gonfaloni; in Pistoia, porta; elsewhere, piviere or podesteria, other quarter subdivision, or vicariat

columns.name: POPOL
columns.dc:description: Popolo, further geographical subdivision within PIVIER

columns.name: NUMVOL
columns.dc:description: Volume in the archival series of the original declaration

columns.name: NUMFOL
columns.dc:description: Folio number (recto or verso) in volume where declaration begins

columns.name: CREANCE
columns.dc:description: Value of private investments in Florins rounded to the nearest florin. Includes all commercial investments excluding value of animals and slaves.

columns.name: CREDPUB
columns.dc:description: Value of public investments (including Monte) in Florins rounded to the nearest florin.

columns.name: TOTAL
columns.dc:description: Total value of assets (private investments, public investments, and value of real estate with the value of the house deducted
